                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1107">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/4313.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Letcher</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 17, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Have been informed that Constitutionalist authorities at Parral have sent an
                    agent to El Paso to induce Americans to return to Parral and reopen their mines
                    and other industries. As many are now disposed to return to this district and
                    are requesting counsel from me on the subject instructions are hereby requested
                    as to how Americans may be advised in the premises.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Letcher</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
